7 ðæt ðæt eage ne mihte open wesan;
8 þa me min wisa and min treowa gefera
9 genealæhte and me his eaxle bebeod.

19 Pur ‘Agnus Dei’ wæron hira ord fruman;
20 an word wæs him eallum and an stefn,
21 swa ðæt him þuhte betwux him sibbe.

28 Swa wæs ðurh stefne gecweden;
29 ða cwæð min lareow: "Andsware,
30 and axa gif her up stigeð."

43 ne læt ðu me hyde hwa ðu wære ær ðe ðe deað gename,
44 ac sege me, and sege me gif ic fare wel to ðam forðsiðe;
45 and ðine word us beoð to lare.

46 Ic wæs Lombard, and wæs gehaten Marcus;
47 ic ðisse worulde cuðe, and ða wuldor lufode
48 ðære nu ælc mon his bogan ontendeð.

58 Þeos weoruld is swa ðus eal forloren
59 ælces gōdes, swa ðu me sægst,
60 and mid yfele hefig and oferþrungen;

61 ac ic bidde ðæt ðu me ðone intingan ætywe,
62 ðæt ic ðæt geseo and ðæt oðrum secge;
63 forðæm ðæt an set on heofonum, and ān her niðer.

73 Heofon ðine stirunge onginneð;
74 ne secge ic ealle, ac ðeah ic hit secge,
75 leoht ðe is forgifen to gode and to yfele,

82 Forðæm, gif ðeos weoruld nu gedwæseð,
83 on eow is ðæt gesceaft, on eow hit sceal beon gesoht;
84 and ic ðe beo nu soðfæst boda.

91 Of lytlum gode ærest he onginneð;
92 ðær he beswicð hine sylfne, and æfter ðam he rynnð,
93 gif his lufu ne gewend his latteow oððe his brydel.

97 Laga sind, ac hwa legeð hi on hand?
98 Nænig, forðæm ðe se hyrde ðe ðone floc lædeð,
99 ceowan mæg, ac he næfð ða toðas toslitene;

109 Se hæfð oðer ðone oðerne ofslægen; and is ðæt sweord
110 cumen mid ðæm stafe, and se oðer mid ðæm oðrum
111 ðurh ða miclan strengðe mot sceal faran;

115 On ðæm lande ðe Adige and Po rigað,
116 solea wlite and wynsumnes findan,
117 ærðæm ðe Federigo hæfde bryge;

130 "Eala, Marcus min," cwæð ic, "wel ðu smeagest;
131 and nu ic oncnawe hwi ðara Levia sunum
132 æhta ne wæron on ðam earde."
